Installation to disk is disabled, so the supported methods are running it as a Live USB or through a VM.
Warning: If run through a VM, there will be no persistent storage in the live session, so persistent data should be kept on the VM's virtual disk or on the host system.

Building
============
Ubuntu System (Tested)
1) Download the latest Ubuntu 14.04 LTS image:
wget http://releases.ubuntu.com/14.04.3/ubuntu-14.04.3-desktop-amd64.iso
2) Install Ubuntu Customisation Kit
sudo apt-get install uck
3) Run UCK
uck
4) Follow prompts and when asked whether you want to run a terminal application, select yes
5) Copy and run the "setup" script within the customisation terminal (ie. in the chroot)
6) Exit the UCK customisation terminal when ready
7) The new ISO image will be built in: ~/tmp/remaster-new-files/livecd.iso

Installation
============
Live USB
--------
Ubuntu System (Tested)
1) Format USB with the FAT filesystem
2) Open Startup Disk Creator
3) Select image, USB drive, and whether persistent storage will be used
4) Select "Make Startup Disk"
5) Give sudo password when requested

Windows
http://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop/create-a-usb-stick-on-windows

Others
https://help.ubuntu.com/community/Installation/FromUSBStick

VM
--------
http://www.wikihow.com/Install-Ubuntu-on-VirtualBox
